Variation in color pattern. (
Fig 1–4
) Sexual dimorphism evident. Males exhibit the same color pattern as the holotype . The only difference is in the intensity of the yellow color in the lateral fieldis more intense in males.Females with the dorsal background color gray to light brown. Head of females are similar in males and females. The vertebral region is bordered by black rounded spots. The size and number of those spots vary and they are absent in some specimens. Pre-scapular spot present. The lateral field exhibits two stripes, a black on the top and white cream below, without spots. Light brown fore and hind limbs with dark brown lines and spots. Ventrally females show the same color of the holotype .

Distribution. The new species is known only from its type locality. (
Fig. 5
)
